Howto change the DNS servers in opoce
---------------------------------------
1. Solaris 10
- cfengine on aiserver-pz
- cd /var/cfengine/master/SYSTEM_FILES/dns
- change all resolv.conf files


2. Solaris 11
- puppet
- cd /home/claeyje/git/Solaris/development/modules/opoce/files/Solaris/etc
- git pull
- update resolv.conf.*
- git commit -am "New dns servers"
- git push
- grep -q Solaris <<< $(pwd) && cd $HOME/git/Solaris/production && pwd && git branch
- git pull origin production && git pull --no-ff
- grep -q Solaris <<< $(pwd) && git push

3. Linux
- puppet
- cd /home/claeyje/git/Linux/development/modules/opoce/files/RedHat/etc
- git pull
- update resolv.conf.*
- git commit -am "New dns servers"
- git push
- grep -q Linux   <<< $(pwd) && cd $HOME/git/Linux/production   && pwd && git branch
- git pull origin production && git pull --no-ff
- grep -q Linux   <<< $(pwd) && git push origin production

